This paper focuses on improving the efficiency and controllability of deep inference, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are a popular tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of resource constraints in IoT applications, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
